ZH: 我们的领导对这个问题显得很无所作为。
EN: Our leader seems very indifferent to this issue.

ZH: 他整天无所作为，什么事情都不处理。
EN: He does nothing all day long, just being idle.

ZH: 这种无所作为的态度让人很失望。
EN: This attitude of doing nothing is very disappointing.

ZH: 员工的怠慢和无所作为导致了项目的失败。
EN: The negligence and idleness of the employees led to the failure of the project.

ZH: 政府的无所作为导致了社会的失序。
EN: The government's idleness led to the disorder in society.

ZH: 他看起来很无所作为，什么都不在乎。
EN: He looks very indifferent, nothing seems to bother him.

ZH: 这种无所作为的态度让人无法接受。
EN: This indifferent attitude is unacceptable.

ZH: 没有行动的计划就等于无所作为。
EN: Having no plan of action is equivalent to being idle.

ZH: 他整天只知道无所作为，从不努力工作。
EN: He is idle all day long, never putting in any effort.

ZH: 这种无所作为的态度会损害团队的工作效率。
EN: This idle attitude will damage the team's efficiency.

ZH: 对待问题要及时解决，而不是无所作为。
EN: Problems need to be handled promptly, not left idle.

ZH: 他一直被批评为无所作为的人。
EN: He has always been criticized as an idle person.

ZH: 面对困难不能选择无所作为。
EN: In the face of difficulties, one cannot choose to be idle.

ZH: 这种无所作为的态度永远无法取得成功。
EN: This idle attitude will never lead to success.

ZH: 将问题置之不理表现出一种无所作为的态度。
EN: Ignoring the problem demonstrates an attitude of idleness.

ZH: 他对困难总是采取无所作为的态度。
EN: He always takes an indifference attitude towards difficulties.

ZH: 领导无所作为只会传递对团队的消极影响。
EN: Leading by being idle will only transmit negative effects to the team.

ZH: 面对挑战不能以无所作为为借口。
EN: We cannot use idleness as an excuse when facing challenges.

ZH: 工作中不能出现无所作为的情况。
EN: There should be no idleness in the workplace.

ZH: 整天无所作为只会让你一事无成。
EN: Being idle all day will lead you to achieve nothing.
